'''Okitsushima Shrine''' (おきつしまじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} enshrined in {{ill|lt=Okinoshima|Q2017235|WD=Q2017235|lt=Okinoshima-chō|1=Okishima}}, {{ill|lt=Ōmihachiman|Q385461|WD=Q385461|1=Ōmihachiman}}, {{ill|lt=Shiga Prefecture|Q131358|WD=Q131358|1=Shiga Prefecture}}. Its {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=former shrine rank|1=Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines|WD=Q712534}} was {{ill|lt=Sonsha|Q134917284|WD=Q134917284|1=Son-sha}}.

=== Enshrined deity ===
* {{ill|lt=Okitsushimahime|Q11350295|WD=Q11350295|lt=Okitsushimahime-no-Mikoto|1=Russian Braille}}

=== Shrine crest ===
Sasa-rindō

=== Origin ===
It is said to have been founded in {{ill|lt=712|Q23521|WD=Q23521|1=712}} (Wadō 5) by {{ill|lt=Fujiwara no Fuhito|Q177517|WD=Q177517|1=Fujiwara no Fuhito}} under imperial command. It is regarded as the {{ill|lt=Myōjin Taisha|Q9610964|WD=Q9610964|1=Myōjin Taisha}} listed in the ''{{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|WD=Q11064932|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}}''<ref>The standard view identifies this as {{ill|lt=Ōshima Shrine Okitsushima Shrine|Q11435100|WD=Q11435100|1=Ōshima & Okitsushima Shrine}}.</ref>.

=== Festival ===
* Annual festival
:Held on May 8.

=== Precinct shrines ===
* Itsukushima Shrine
* Yamagami Shrine

=== Cultural properties, etc. ===
* ''Okitsushima Jinja-ki'' - shrine record written in {{ill|lt=1525|Q6314|WD=Q6314|1=1525}} (Daiei 5)
* ''Benzaiten-ki'' (Kyōhō 19)

